The paper deals with the problem of blind deconvolution, which is a common problem in many areas of science and technology, including image processing (cs.CV), wireless communications (cs.IT), and optimization (cs.NA). The paper proposes a numerical algorithm that is efficient and robust against noise, which suggests that it may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or signal processing (cs.SI).
